'''九龍蟲'''（學名：{{lang|la|''Ulomoides dermestoides''}}），俗稱'''楊蟲'''或'''洋蟲'''，是一種體型細小的[[鞘翅目|鞘翅目]][[拟步行虫科|拟步行虫科]]的[[物种|物种]]。原生於[[亚洲|亚洲]]，東亞地區坊間認為此蟲具醫療[[哮喘|哮喘]]、[[癌症|癌症]]等病的功效而飼養，亦因此而隨同人口遷徙而散佈至全世界。

==形態描述==
表面呈[[深啡色|深啡色]]至黑色。體積如[[穀牛|穀牛]]般細小：長5毫米，寬1.5毫米。
從卵孵化至變態成蟲，需時約6-7週。

==歷史==
如同其他同屬''[[Ulomoides|Ulomoides]]''屬的物種，九龍蟲原是一種穀物或穀物製品的害蟲，常見於麵包或相關食物製品。牠主要棲息於草原和沙漠中。在日本及大中華地區民間相信本物種具醫治腰背痛、咳嗽及諸如哮喘等呼吸系統疾病的功效<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/610028/ |last1=Chu |first1=G.S.T. |last2=Palmieri |first2=J.R. |last3=Sullivan |first3=J.T. |year=1977 |title=Beetle-eating: A Malaysia folk medical practice and its public health implications |journal=''[[Tropical_Geographic_Medicine|Tropical Geographic Medicine]]'' |volume=29 |pages=422–427 |date=1977-12 |access-date=2020-11-16 |pmid=610028 |language=en }}</ref>。
這種甲蟲大約在公元2000年時得到國際上的關注，原因是在[[阿根廷|阿根廷]]及[[巴西|巴西]]的居民進口及進食這種昆蟲：他們在家居後院培育，並透過社區網絡分發及宣傳食用這種昆蟲物種的活體，旨在紆緩或治療諸如[[哮喘|哮喘]]、[[柏金遜症|柏金遜症]]、[[糖尿病|糖尿病]]、[[關節炎|關節炎]]、[[HIV|HIV]]及癌症等多種疾病<ref name = "Crespo">Rosana Crespo, M. Luciana Villaverde, Juan R. Girotti, Alba Güerci, M. Patricia Juárez, Margarita G. de Bravo. 2011. Cytotoxic and genotoxic effects of defence secretion of ''Ulomoides dermestoides'' on A549 cells. ''Journal of Ethnopharmacology'' 136 (1): 204–209. doi:10.1016/j.jep.2011.04.056</ref>。 At that time, it was commonly called "the chinese weevil" (or "gorgojo chino"), although it is not related to true <!-- [[weevil|weevil]] -->[[象鼻蟲|象鼻蟲]]s.

==習性==
九龍蟲進食的次數很頻密。雖然餵飼牠的食材相對較為矜貴，但卻非常粗生，能在不見天日的[[密閉空間|密閉空間]]裡大量繁殖。

==藥用價值==
坊間習慣以各種不同的中藥材，例如：[[蓮子|蓮子]]或[[淮山|淮山]]來餵飼九龍蟲，並使其排出不同顏色（有白色到[[咖啡色|咖啡色]]）的[[糞便|糞便]]。這些糞便一般沒有臭味，並具藥用價值。只需將其篩成粉末狀，在傷口出血時外敷，具顯著的止血功用。

據文獻估計，每年服用這些九龍蟲或其糞便的民眾達數以千計，而每人又服用數以千計的蟲體<ref name = "Crespo"/>。至於這些蟲體的藥效紛紜，though none confirming the claims of curative properties. The chemicals, primarily <!-- [[quinone|quinone]] -->[[醌|醌]]s, that the beetles produce as defensive compounds are capable of killing cells (significant <!-- [[cytotoxicity|cytotoxicity]] -->[[細胞毒性|細胞毒性]]), affecting both healthy and cancerous tissues,<ref name = "Crespo"/> and overconsumption of beetles can lead to serious health complications such as pneumonia,<ref>Bhupinder S. Natt, M.D., Janet M. Campion, M.D., and Kenneth S. Knox, M.D.. Acute Eosinophilic Pneumonia Associated with Ingestion of ''Ulomoides dermestoides'' Larvae (“Chinese Beetles”). ''Annals of the American Thoracic Society'' 2014;10:1667-1668. doi: 10.1513/AnnalsATS.201410-483LE</ref> and thus contraindicated as a medical treatment. Diluted extract from these beetles has been found to have anti-inflammatory properties, but at higher doses the toxic effects predominate.<ref>Santos, R.C.V., Lunardelli, A., Caberlon, E. et al. (2010) Anti-inflammatory and Immunomodulatory Effects of ''Ulomoides dermestoides'' on Induced Pleurisy in Rats and Lymphoproliferation ''In Vitro''.  ''Inflammation'' 33: 173. doi:10.1007/s10753-009-9171-x</ref>

